  "final_text": "I'll check the reset-cause flags in RCC and inspect both watchdog peripherals in parallel.\nThe RCC output was truncated \u2014 let me pull the reset-cause flags from the saved file.\nHere's the full picture from all three peripherals:\n\n---\n\n## Reset cause \u2014 **not a watchdog reset**\n\n**RCC_CSR** (raw `0x1C000000`) \u2014 reset flags (RMVF=0, so flags are still valid from last reset):\n\n| Flag | Value | Meaning |\n|---|---|---|\n| `IWDGRSTF` (bit 29) | **0** | \u274c No IWDG reset |\n| `WWDGRSTF` (bit 30) | **0** | \u274c No WWDG reset |\n| `SFTRSTF` (bit 28) | **1** | \u2705 Software reset (debugger attach / `SYSRESETREQ`) |\n| `BORRSTF` (bit 27) | **1** | \u2705 Brown-out reset recorded |\n| `PINRSTF` (bit 26) | **1** | \u2705 NRST pin reset recorded |\n\nThe last reset was a **software/debugger reset** \u2014 the three flags set together (`SFTRSTF + BORRSTF + PINRSTF`) is the classic NUCLEO power-cycle + ST-LINK probe reset signature. Neither watchdog fired.\n\n---\n\n## Watchdog peripheral state\n\n**WWDG \u2014 disabled**\n- `WDGA` = 0 \u2192 the window watchdog has **not been activated**. It's fully off. Once set, WDGA is hardware-clearable only by reset, so this is definitive.\n\n**IWDG \u2014 at power-on defaults, not explicitly started**\n- `PR` = 0 (\u00f74 prescaler, reset default)\n- `RLR` = 0xFFF / 4095 (max reload, reset default)\n- `WINR` = 0xFFF (no early-reload window restriction, reset default)\n- `SR` = 0x0 \u2014 no pending prescaler/reload/window update operations\n\nAll IWDG registers are at their reset defaults; no software has written the start key (`0xCCCC` to KR). **One caveat:** if the `IWDG_SW` option byte is **cleared** (hardware-start mode), the IWDG begins counting automatically at power-on regardless of software. If you want to rule that out, I can read the option bytes \u2014 just say the word.\n\n---\n\n**Bottom line:** Neither IWDG nor WWDG caused the reset. The target last reset via a software/debugger reset. The WWDG is off; the IWDG is at defaults and appears unstarted by software (pending option-byte confirmation)."
